5296 /// parseDirectiveCVDefRange
5297 /// ::= .cv_def_range RangeStart RangeEnd (GapStart GapEnd)*, bytes*
5298 bool MasmParser::parseDirectiveCVDefRange() {
5299  SMLoc Loc;
5300  std::vector<std::pair<const MCSymbol *, const MCSymbol *>> Ranges;
5301  while (getLexer().is(AsmToken::Identifier)) {
5302  Loc = getLexer().getLoc();
5303  StringRef GapStartName;
5304  if (parseIdentifier(GapStartName))
5305  return Error(Loc, "expected identifier in directive");
5306  MCSymbol *GapStartSym = getContext().getOrCreateSymbol(GapStartName);
5307 
5308  Loc = getLexer().getLoc();
5309  StringRef GapEndName;
5310  if (parseIdentifier(GapEndName))
5311  return Error(Loc, "expected identifier in directive");
5312  MCSymbol *GapEndSym = getContext().getOrCreateSymbol(GapEndName);
5313 
5314  Ranges.push_back({GapStartSym, GapEndSym});
5315  }
5316 
5317  StringRef CVDefRangeTypeStr;
5318  if (parseToken(
5319  AsmToken::Comma,
5320  "expected comma before def_range type in .cv_def_range directive") ||
5321  parseIdentifier(CVDefRangeTypeStr))
5322  return Error(Loc, "expected def_range type in directive");
5323 
5324  StringMap<CVDefRangeType>::const_iterator CVTypeIt =
5325  CVDefRangeTypeMap.find(CVDefRangeTypeStr);
5326  CVDefRangeType CVDRType = (CVTypeIt == CVDefRangeTypeMap.end())
5327  ? CVDR_DEFRANGE
5328  : CVTypeIt->getValue();
5329  switch (CVDRType) {
5330  case CVDR_DEFRANGE_REGISTER: {
5331  int64_t DRRegister;
5332  if (parseToken(AsmToken::Comma, "expected comma before register number in "
5333  ".cv_def_range directive") ||
5334  parseAbsoluteExpression(DRRegister))
5335  return Error(Loc, "expected register number");
5336 
5337  codeview::DefRangeRegisterHeader DRHdr;
5338  DRHdr.Register = DRRegister;
5339  DRHdr.MayHaveNoName = 0;
5340  getStreamer().emitCVDefRangeDirective(Ranges, DRHdr);
5341  break;
5342  }
5343  case CVDR_DEFRANGE_FRAMEPOINTER_REL: {
5344  int64_t DROffset;
5345  if (parseToken(AsmToken::Comma,
5346  "expected comma before offset in .cv_def_range directive") ||
5347  parseAbsoluteExpression(DROffset))
5348  return Error(Loc, "expected offset value");
5349 
5350  codeview::DefRangeFramePointerRelHeader DRHdr;
5351  DRHdr.Offset = DROffset;
5352  getStreamer().emitCVDefRangeDirective(Ranges, DRHdr);
5353  break;
5354  }
5355  case CVDR_DEFRANGE_SUBFIELD_REGISTER: {
5356  int64_t DRRegister;
5357  int64_t DROffsetInParent;
5358  if (parseToken(AsmToken::Comma, "expected comma before register number in "
5359  ".cv_def_range directive") ||
5360  parseAbsoluteExpression(DRRegister))
5361  return Error(Loc, "expected register number");
5362  if (parseToken(AsmToken::Comma,
5363  "expected comma before offset in .cv_def_range directive") ||
5364  parseAbsoluteExpression(DROffsetInParent))
5365  return Error(Loc, "expected offset value");
5366 
5367  codeview::DefRangeSubfieldRegisterHeader DRHdr;
5368  DRHdr.Register = DRRegister;
5369  DRHdr.MayHaveNoName = 0;
5370  DRHdr.OffsetInParent = DROffsetInParent;
5371  getStreamer().emitCVDefRangeDirective(Ranges, DRHdr);
5372  break;
5373  }
5374  case CVDR_DEFRANGE_REGISTER_REL: {
5375  int64_t DRRegister;
5376  int64_t DRFlags;
5377  int64_t DRBasePointerOffset;
5378  if (parseToken(AsmToken::Comma, "expected comma before register number in "
5379  ".cv_def_range directive") ||
5380  parseAbsoluteExpression(DRRegister))
5381  return Error(Loc, "expected register value");
5382  if (parseToken(
5383  AsmToken::Comma,
5384  "expected comma before flag value in .cv_def_range directive") ||
5385  parseAbsoluteExpression(DRFlags))
5386  return Error(Loc, "expected flag value");
5387  if (parseToken(AsmToken::Comma, "expected comma before base pointer offset "
5388  "in .cv_def_range directive") ||
5389  parseAbsoluteExpression(DRBasePointerOffset))
5390  return Error(Loc, "expected base pointer offset value");
5391 
5392  codeview::DefRangeRegisterRelHeader DRHdr;
5393  DRHdr.Register = DRRegister;
5394  DRHdr.Flags = DRFlags;
5395  DRHdr.BasePointerOffset = DRBasePointerOffset;
5396  getStreamer().emitCVDefRangeDirective(Ranges, DRHdr);
5397  break;
5398  }
5399  default:
5400  return Error(Loc, "unexpected def_range type in .cv_def_range directive");
5401  }
5402  return true;
5403 }

5406 /// ::= .cv_stringtable "string"
5407 bool MasmParser::parseDirectiveCVString() {
5408  std::string Data;

5410  return addErrorSuffix(" in '.cv_string' directive");
5411

5414  getCVContext().addToStringTable(Data);

5490 /// parseDirectiveCFIStartProc
5491 /// ::= .cfi_startproc [simple]
5492 bool MasmParser::parseDirectiveCFIStartProc() {
5493  StringRef Simple;
5494  if (!parseOptionalToken(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
5495  if (check(parseIdentifier(Simple) || Simple != "simple",
5496  "unexpected token") ||
5497  parseToken(AsmToken::EndOfStatement))
5498  return addErrorSuffix(" in '.cfi_startproc' directive");
5499  }
5500 
5501  // TODO(kristina): Deal with a corner case of incorrect diagnostic context
5502  // being produced if this directive is emitted as part of preprocessor macro
5503  // expansion which can *ONLY* happen if Clang's cc1as is the API consumer.
5504  // Tools like llvm-mc on the other hand are not affected by it, and report
5505  // correct context information.
5506  getStreamer().emitCFIStartProc(!Simple.empty(), Lexer.getLoc());
5507  return false;
5508 }

5512 bool MasmParser::parseDirectiveCFIEndProc() {
5513  getStreamer().emitCFIEndProc();
5514  return false;
5515 }

5517 /// parse register name or number.
5518 bool MasmParser::parseRegisterOrRegisterNumber(int64_t &Register,
5519  SMLoc DirectiveLoc) {
5520  MCRegister RegNo;
5521 
5522  if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::Integer)) {
5523  if (getTargetParser().parseRegister(RegNo, DirectiveLoc, DirectiveLoc))
5524  return true;
5525  Register = getContext().getRegisterInfo()->getDwarfRegNum(RegNo, true);
5526  } else
5527  return parseAbsoluteExpression(Register);
5528 
5529  return false;
5530 }

5627 static bool isValidEncoding(int64_t Encoding) {
5628  if (Encoding & ~0xff)
5629  return false;
5630 
5631  if (Encoding == dwarf::DW_EH_PE_omit)
5632  return true;
5633 
5634  const unsigned Format = Encoding & 0xf;
5635  if (Format != dwarf::DW_EH_PE_absptr && Format != dwarf::DW_EH_PE_udata2 &&
5636  Format != dwarf::DW_EH_PE_udata4 && Format != dwarf::DW_EH_PE_udata8 &&
5637  Format != dwarf::DW_EH_PE_sdata2 && Format != dwarf::DW_EH_PE_sdata4 &&
5638  Format != dwarf::DW_EH_PE_sdata8 && Format != dwarf::DW_EH_PE_signed)
5639  return false;
5640 
5641  const unsigned Application = Encoding & 0x70;
5642  if (Application != dwarf::DW_EH_PE_absptr &&
5643  Application != dwarf::DW_EH_PE_pcrel)
5644  return false;
5645 
5646  return true;
5647 }
5648 
5649 /// parseDirectiveCFIPersonalityOrLsda
5650 /// IsPersonality true for cfi_personality, false for cfi_lsda
5651 /// ::= .cfi_personality encoding, [symbol_name]
5652 /// ::= .cfi_lsda encoding, [symbol_name]
5653 bool MasmParser::parseDirectiveCFIPersonalityOrLsda(bool IsPersonality) {
5654  int64_t Encoding = 0;
5655  if (parseAbsoluteExpression(Encoding))
5656  return true;
5657  if (Encoding == dwarf::DW_EH_PE_omit)
5658  return false;
5659 
5660  StringRef Name;
5661  if (check(!isValidEncoding(Encoding), "unsupported encoding.") ||
5662  parseToken(AsmToken::Comma, "unexpected token in directive") ||
5663  check(parseIdentifier(Name), "expected identifier in directive"))
5664  return true;
5665 
5666  MCSymbol *Sym = getContext().getOrCreateSymbol(Name);
5667 
5668  if (IsPersonality)
5669  getStreamer().emitCFIPersonality(Sym, Encoding);
5670  else
5671  getStreamer().emitCFILsda(Sym, Encoding);
5672  return false;
5673 }

5712 /// parseDirectiveCFIEscape

5714 bool MasmParser::parseDirectiveCFIEscape() {
5715  std::string Values;

5718  return true;
5719 
5720  Values.push_back((uint8_t)CurrValue);
5721 
5722  while (getLexer().is(AsmToken::Comma)) {
5723  Lex();
5724 
5725  if (parseAbsoluteExpression(CurrValue))
5726  return true;
5727

5729  }

5767 /// parseDirectiveMacro
5768 /// ::= name macro [parameters]
5769 /// ["LOCAL" identifiers]
5770 /// parameters ::= parameter [, parameter]*
5771 /// parameter ::= name ":" qualifier
5772 /// qualifier ::= "req" | "vararg" | "=" macro_argument
5773 bool MasmParser::parseDirectiveMacro(StringRef Name, SMLoc NameLoc) {
5774  MCAsmMacroParameters Parameters;
5775  while (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
5776  if (!Parameters.empty() && Parameters.back().Vararg)
5777  return Error(Lexer.getLoc(),
5778  "Vararg parameter '" + Parameters.back().Name +
5779  "' should be last in the list of parameters");
5780 
5781  MCAsmMacroParameter Parameter;
5782  if (parseIdentifier(Parameter.Name))
5783  return TokError("expected identifier in 'macro' directive");
5784 
5785  // Emit an error if two (or more) named parameters share the same name.
5786  for (const MCAsmMacroParameter& CurrParam : Parameters)
5787  if (CurrParam.Name.equals_insensitive(Parameter.Name))
5788  return TokError("macro '" + Name + "' has multiple parameters"
5789  " named '" + Parameter.Name + "'");
5790 
5791  if (Lexer.is(AsmToken::Colon)) {
5792  Lex(); // consume ':'
5793 
5794  if (parseOptionalToken(AsmToken::Equal)) {
5795  // Default value
5796  SMLoc ParamLoc;
5797 
5798  ParamLoc = Lexer.getLoc();
5799  if (parseMacroArgument(nullptr, Parameter.Value))
5800  return true;
5801  } else {
5802  SMLoc QualLoc;
5803  StringRef Qualifier;
5804 
5805  QualLoc = Lexer.getLoc();
5806  if (parseIdentifier(Qualifier))
5807  return Error(QualLoc, "missing parameter qualifier for "
5808  "'" +
5809  Parameter.Name + "' in macro '" + Name +
5810  "'");
5811 
5812  if (Qualifier.equals_insensitive("req"))
5813  Parameter.Required = true;
5814  else if (Qualifier.equals_insensitive("vararg"))
5815  Parameter.Vararg = true;
5816  else
5817  return Error(QualLoc,
5818  Qualifier + " is not a valid parameter qualifier for '" +
5819  Parameter.Name + "' in macro '" + Name + "'");
5820  }
5821  }
5822 
5823  Parameters.push_back(std::move(Parameter));
5824 
5825  if (getLexer().is(AsmToken::Comma))
5826  Lex();
5827  }
5828 
5829  // Eat just the end of statement.
5830  Lexer.Lex();
5831 
5832  std::vector<std::string> Locals;
5833  if (getTok().is(AsmToken::Identifier) &&
5834  getTok().getIdentifier().equals_insensitive("local")) {
5835  Lex(); // Eat the LOCAL directive.
5836 
5837  StringRef ID;
5838  while (true) {
5839  if (parseIdentifier(ID))
5840  return true;
5841  Locals.push_back(ID.lower());
5842 
5843  // If we see a comma, continue (and allow line continuation).
5844  if (!parseOptionalToken(AsmToken::Comma))
5845  break;
5846  parseOptionalToken(AsmToken::EndOfStatement);
5847  }
5848  }
5849 
5850  // Consuming deferred text, so use Lexer.Lex to ignore Lexing Errors.
5851  AsmToken EndToken, StartToken = getTok();
5852  unsigned MacroDepth = 0;
5853  bool IsMacroFunction = false;
5854  // Lex the macro definition.
5855  while (true) {
5856  // Ignore Lexing errors in macros.
5857  while (Lexer.is(AsmToken::Error)) {
5858  Lexer.Lex();
5859  }
5860 
5861  // Check whether we have reached the end of the file.
5862  if (getLexer().is(AsmToken::Eof))
5863  return Error(NameLoc, "no matching 'endm' in definition");
5864 
5865  // Otherwise, check whether we have reached the 'endm'... and determine if
5866  // this is a macro function.
5867  if (getLexer().is(AsmToken::Identifier)) {
5868  if (getTok().getIdentifier().equals_insensitive("endm")) {
5869  if (MacroDepth == 0) { // Outermost macro.
5870  EndToken = getTok();
5871  Lexer.Lex();
5872  if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement))
5873  return TokError("unexpected token in '" + EndToken.getIdentifier() +
5874  "' directive");
5875  break;
5876  } else {
5877  // Otherwise we just found the end of an inner macro.
5878  --MacroDepth;
5879  }
5880  } else if (getTok().getIdentifier().equals_insensitive("exitm")) {
5881  if (MacroDepth == 0 && peekTok().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
5882  IsMacroFunction = true;
5883  }
5884  } else if (isMacroLikeDirective()) {
5885  // We allow nested macros. Those aren't instantiated until the
5886  // outermost macro is expanded so just ignore them for now.
5887  ++MacroDepth;
5888  }
5889  }
5890 
5891  // Otherwise, scan til the end of the statement.
5892  eatToEndOfStatement();
5893  }
5894 
5895  if (getContext().lookupMacro(Name.lower())) {
5896  return Error(NameLoc, "macro '" + Name + "' is already defined");
5897  }
5898 
5899  const char *BodyStart = StartToken.getLoc().getPointer();
5900  const char *BodyEnd = EndToken.getLoc().getPointer();
5901  StringRef Body = StringRef(BodyStart, BodyEnd - BodyStart);
5902  MCAsmMacro Macro(Name, Body, std::move(Parameters), std::move(Locals),
5903  IsMacroFunction);
5904  DEBUG_WITH_TYPE("asm-macros", dbgs() << "Defining new macro:\n";
5905  Macro.dump());
5906  getContext().defineMacro(Name.lower(), std::move(Macro));
5907  return false;
5908 }
5909 
5910 /// parseDirectiveExitMacro
5911 /// ::= "exitm" [textitem]
5912 bool MasmParser::parseDirectiveExitMacro(SMLoc DirectiveLoc,
5913  StringRef Directive,
5914  std::string &Value) {
5915  SMLoc EndLoc = getTok().getLoc();
5916  if (getTok().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement) && parseTextItem(Value))
5917  return Error(EndLoc,
5918  "unable to parse text item in '" + Directive + "' directive");
5919  eatToEndOfStatement();
5920 
5921  if (!isInsideMacroInstantiation())
5922  return TokError("unexpected '" + Directive + "' in file, "
5923  "no current macro definition");
5924 
5925  // Exit all conditionals that are active in the current macro.
5926  while (TheCondStack.size() != ActiveMacros.back()->CondStackDepth) {
5927  TheCondState = TheCondStack.back();
5928  TheCondStack.pop_back();
5929  }
5930 
5931  handleMacroExit();
5932  return false;
5933 }
5934 
5935 /// parseDirectiveEndMacro
5936 /// ::= endm
5937 bool MasmParser::parseDirectiveEndMacro(StringRef Directive) {
5938  if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement))
5939  return TokError("unexpected token in '" + Directive + "' directive");
5940 
5941  // If we are inside a macro instantiation, terminate the current
5942  // instantiation.
5943  if (isInsideMacroInstantiation()) {
5944  handleMacroExit();
5945  return false;
5946  }
5947 
5948  // Otherwise, this .endmacro is a stray entry in the file; well formed
5949  // .endmacro directives are handled during the macro definition parsing.
5950  return TokError("unexpected '" + Directive + "' in file, "
5951  "no current macro definition");
5952 }
5953 
5954 /// parseDirectivePurgeMacro
5955 /// ::= purge identifier ( , identifier )*
5956 bool MasmParser::parseDirectivePurgeMacro(SMLoc DirectiveLoc) {
5957  StringRef Name;
5958  while (true) {
5959  SMLoc NameLoc;
5960  if (parseTokenLoc(NameLoc) ||
5961  check(parseIdentifier(Name), NameLoc,
5962  "expected identifier in 'purge' directive"))
5963  return true;
5964 
5965  DEBUG_WITH_TYPE("asm-macros", dbgs()
5966  << "Un-defining macro: " << Name << "\n");
5967  if (!getContext().lookupMacro(Name.lower()))
5968  return Error(NameLoc, "macro '" + Name + "' is not defined");
5969  getContext().undefineMacro(Name.lower());
5970 
5971  if (!parseOptionalToken(AsmToken::Comma))
5972  break;
5973  parseOptionalToken(AsmToken::EndOfStatement);
5974  }
5975 
5976  return false;
5977 }
5978 
5979 bool MasmParser::parseDirectiveExtern() {
5980  // .extern is the default - but we still need to take any provided type info.
5981  auto parseOp = [&]() -> bool {
5982  StringRef Name;
5983  SMLoc NameLoc = getTok().getLoc();
5984  if (parseIdentifier(Name))
5985  return Error(NameLoc, "expected name");
5986  if (parseToken(AsmToken::Colon))
5987  return true;
5988 
5989  StringRef TypeName;
5990  SMLoc TypeLoc = getTok().getLoc();
5991  if (parseIdentifier(TypeName))
5992  return Error(TypeLoc, "expected type");
5993  if (!TypeName.equals_insensitive("proc")) {
5994  AsmTypeInfo Type;
5995  if (lookUpType(TypeName, Type))
5996  return Error(TypeLoc, "unrecognized type");
5997  KnownType[Name.lower()] = Type;
5998  }
5999 
6000  MCSymbol *Sym = getContext().getOrCreateSymbol(Name);
6001  Sym->setExternal(true);
6002  getStreamer().emitSymbolAttribute(Sym, MCSA_Extern);
6003 
6004  return false;
6005  };
6006 
6007  if (parseMany(parseOp))
6008  return addErrorSuffix(" in directive 'extern'");
6009  return false;
6010 }
6011 
6012 /// parseDirectiveSymbolAttribute
6013 /// ::= { ".globl", ".weak", ... } [ identifier ( , identifier )* ]
6014 bool MasmParser::parseDirectiveSymbolAttribute(MCSymbolAttr Attr) {
6015  auto parseOp = [&]() -> bool {
6016  StringRef Name;
6017  SMLoc Loc = getTok().getLoc();
6018  if (parseIdentifier(Name))
6019  return Error(Loc, "expected identifier");
6020  MCSymbol *Sym = getContext().getOrCreateSymbol(Name);
6021 
6022  // Assembler local symbols don't make any sense here. Complain loudly.
6023  if (Sym->isTemporary())
6024  return Error(Loc, "non-local symbol required");
6025 
6026  if (!getStreamer().emitSymbolAttribute(Sym, Attr))
6027  return Error(Loc, "unable to emit symbol attribute");
6028  return false;
6029  };
6030 
6031  if (parseMany(parseOp))
6032  return addErrorSuffix(" in directive");
6033  return false;
6034 }
6035 
6036 /// parseDirectiveComm
6037 /// ::= ( .comm | .lcomm ) identifier , size_expression [ , align_expression ]
6038 bool MasmParser::parseDirectiveComm(bool IsLocal) {
6039  if (checkForValidSection())
6040  return true;
6041 
6042  SMLoc IDLoc = getLexer().getLoc();
6043  StringRef Name;
6044  if (parseIdentifier(Name))
6045  return TokError("expected identifier in directive");
6046 
6047  // Handle the identifier as the key symbol.
6048  MCSymbol *Sym = getContext().getOrCreateSymbol(Name);
6049 
6050  if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::Comma))
6051  return TokError("unexpected token in directive");
6052  Lex();
6053 
6054  int64_t Size;
6055  SMLoc SizeLoc = getLexer().getLoc();
6056  if (parseAbsoluteExpression(Size))
6057  return true;
6058 
6059  int64_t Pow2Alignment = 0;
6060  SMLoc Pow2AlignmentLoc;
6061  if (getLexer().is(AsmToken::Comma)) {
6062  Lex();
6063  Pow2AlignmentLoc = getLexer().getLoc();
6064  if (parseAbsoluteExpression(Pow2Alignment))
6065  return true;
6066 
6067  LCOMM::LCOMMType LCOMM = Lexer.getMAI().getLCOMMDirectiveAlignmentType();
6068  if (IsLocal && LCOMM == LCOMM::NoAlignment)
6069  return Error(Pow2AlignmentLoc, "alignment not supported on this target");
6070 
6071  // If this target takes alignments in bytes (not log) validate and convert.
6072  if ((!IsLocal && Lexer.getMAI().getCOMMDirectiveAlignmentIsInBytes()) ||
6073  (IsLocal && LCOMM == LCOMM::ByteAlignment)) {
6074  if (!isPowerOf2_64(Pow2Alignment))
6075  return Error(Pow2AlignmentLoc, "alignment must be a power of 2");
6076  Pow2Alignment = Log2_64(Pow2Alignment);
6077  }
6078  }
6079 
6080  if (parseEOL())
6081  return true;
6082 
6083  // NOTE: a size of zero for a .comm should create a undefined symbol
6084  // but a size of .lcomm creates a bss symbol of size zero.
6085  if (Size < 0)
6086  return Error(SizeLoc, "invalid '.comm' or '.lcomm' directive size, can't "
6087  "be less than zero");
6088 
6089  // NOTE: The alignment in the directive is a power of 2 value, the assembler
6090  // may internally end up wanting an alignment in bytes.
6091  // FIXME: Diagnose overflow.
6092  if (Pow2Alignment < 0)
6093  return Error(Pow2AlignmentLoc, "invalid '.comm' or '.lcomm' directive "
6094  "alignment, can't be less than zero");
6095 
6096  Sym->redefineIfPossible();
6097  if (!Sym->isUndefined())
6098  return Error(IDLoc, "invalid symbol redefinition");
6099 
6100  // Create the Symbol as a common or local common with Size and Pow2Alignment.
6101  if (IsLocal) {
6102  getStreamer().emitLocalCommonSymbol(Sym, Size,
6103  Align(1ULL << Pow2Alignment));
6104  return false;
6105  }
6106 
6107  getStreamer().emitCommonSymbol(Sym, Size, Align(1ULL << Pow2Alignment));
6108  return false;
6109 }
6110 
6111 /// parseDirectiveComment
6112 /// ::= comment delimiter [[text]]
6113 /// [[text]]
6114 /// [[text]] delimiter [[text]]
6115 bool MasmParser::parseDirectiveComment(SMLoc DirectiveLoc) {
6116  std::string FirstLine = parseStringTo(AsmToken::EndOfStatement);
6117  size_t DelimiterEnd = FirstLine.find_first_of("\b\t\v\f\r\x1A ");
6118  StringRef Delimiter = StringRef(FirstLine).take_front(DelimiterEnd);
6119  if (Delimiter.empty())
6120  return Error(DirectiveLoc, "no delimiter in 'comment' directive");
6121  do {
6122  if (getTok().is(AsmToken::Eof))
6123  return Error(DirectiveLoc, "unmatched delimiter in 'comment' directive");
6124  Lex(); // eat end of statement
6125  } while (
6126  !StringRef(parseStringTo(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)).contains(Delimiter));
6127  return parseEOL();
6128 }
6129 
6130 /// parseDirectiveInclude
6131 /// ::= include <filename>
6132 /// | include filename
6133 bool MasmParser::parseDirectiveInclude() {
6134  // Allow the strings to have escaped octal character sequence.
6135  std::string Filename;
6136  SMLoc IncludeLoc = getTok().getLoc();
6137 
6138  if (parseAngleBracketString(Filename))
6139  Filename = parseStringTo(AsmToken::EndOfStatement);
6140  if (check(Filename.empty(), "missing filename in 'include' directive") ||
6141  check(getTok().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement),
6142  "unexpected token in 'include' directive") ||
6143  // Attempt to switch the lexer to the included file before consuming the
6144  // end of statement to avoid losing it when we switch.
6145  check(enterIncludeFile(Filename), IncludeLoc,
6146  "Could not find include file '" + Filename + "'"))
6147  return true;
6148 
6149  return false;
6150 }
6151 
6152 /// parseDirectiveIf
6153 /// ::= .if{,eq,ge,gt,le,lt,ne} expression
6154 bool MasmParser::parseDirectiveIf(SMLoc DirectiveLoc, DirectiveKind DirKind) {
6155  TheCondStack.push_back(TheCondState);
6156  TheCondState.TheCond = AsmCond::IfCond;
6157  if (TheCondState.Ignore) {
6158  eatToEndOfStatement();
6159  } else {
6160  int64_t ExprValue;
6161  if (parseAbsoluteExpression(ExprValue) || parseEOL())
6162  return true;
6163 
6164  switch (DirKind) {
6165  default:
6166  llvm_unreachable("unsupported directive");
6167  case DK_IF:
6168  break;
6169  case DK_IFE:
6170  ExprValue = ExprValue == 0;
6171  break;
6172  }
6173 
6174  TheCondState.CondMet = ExprValue;
6175  TheCondState.Ignore = !TheCondState.CondMet;
6176  }
6177 
6178  return false;
6179 }
6180 
6181 /// parseDirectiveIfb
6182 /// ::= .ifb textitem
6183 bool MasmParser::parseDirectiveIfb(SMLoc DirectiveLoc, bool ExpectBlank) {
6184  TheCondStack.push_back(TheCondState);
6185  TheCondState.TheCond = AsmCond::IfCond;
6186 
6187  if (TheCondState.Ignore) {
6188  eatToEndOfStatement();
6189  } else {
6190  std::string Str;
6191  if (parseTextItem(Str))
6192  return TokError("expected text item parameter for 'ifb' directive");
6193 
6194  if (parseEOL())
6195  return true;
6196 
6197  TheCondState.CondMet = ExpectBlank == Str.empty();
6198  TheCondState.Ignore = !TheCondState.CondMet;
6199  }
6200 
6201  return false;
6202 }
6203 
6204 /// parseDirectiveIfidn
6205 /// ::= ifidn textitem, textitem
6206 bool MasmParser::parseDirectiveIfidn(SMLoc DirectiveLoc, bool ExpectEqual,
6207  bool CaseInsensitive) {
6208  std::string String1, String2;
6209 
6210  if (parseTextItem(String1)) {
6211  if (ExpectEqual)
6212  return TokError("expected text item parameter for 'ifidn' directive");
6213  return TokError("expected text item parameter for 'ifdif' directive");
6214  }
6215 
6216  if (Lexer.isNot(AsmToken::Comma)) {
6217  if (ExpectEqual)
6218  return TokError(
6219  "expected comma after first string for 'ifidn' directive");
6220  return TokError("expected comma after first string for 'ifdif' directive");
6221  }
6222  Lex();
6223 
6224  if (parseTextItem(String2)) {
6225  if (ExpectEqual)
6226  return TokError("expected text item parameter for 'ifidn' directive");
6227  return TokError("expected text item parameter for 'ifdif' directive");
6228  }
6229 
6230  TheCondStack.push_back(TheCondState);
6231  TheCondState.TheCond = AsmCond::IfCond;
6232  if (CaseInsensitive)
6233  TheCondState.CondMet =
6234  ExpectEqual == (StringRef(String1).equals_insensitive(String2));
6235  else
6236  TheCondState.CondMet = ExpectEqual == (String1 == String2);
6237  TheCondState.Ignore = !TheCondState.CondMet;
6238 
6239  return false;
6240 }
6241 
6242 /// parseDirectiveIfdef
6243 /// ::= ifdef symbol
6244 /// | ifdef variable
6245 bool MasmParser::parseDirectiveIfdef(SMLoc DirectiveLoc, bool expect_defined) {
6246  TheCondStack.push_back(TheCondState);
6247  TheCondState.TheCond = AsmCond::IfCond;
6248 
6249  if (TheCondState.Ignore) {
6250  eatToEndOfStatement();
6251  } else {
6252  bool is_defined = false;
6253  MCRegister Reg;
6254  SMLoc StartLoc, EndLoc;
6255  is_defined = (getTargetParser().tryParseRegister(Reg, StartLoc, EndLoc) ==
6256  MatchOperand_Success);
6257  if (!is_defined) {
6258  StringRef Name;
6259  if (check(parseIdentifier(Name), "expected identifier after 'ifdef'") ||
6260  parseEOL())
6261  return true;
6262 
6263  if (BuiltinSymbolMap.find(Name.lower()) != BuiltinSymbolMap.end()) {
6264  is_defined = true;
6265  } else if (Variables.find(Name.lower()) != Variables.end()) {
6266  is_defined = true;
6267  } else {
6268  MCSymbol *Sym = getContext().lookupSymbol(Name.lower());
6269  is_defined = (Sym && !Sym->isUndefined(false));
6270  }
6271  }
6272 
6273  TheCondState.CondMet = (is_defined == expect_defined);
6274  TheCondState.Ignore = !TheCondState.CondMet;
6275  }
6276 
6277  return false;
6278 }

6280 /// parseDirectiveElseIf
6281 /// ::= elseif expression
6282 bool MasmParser::parseDirectiveElseIf(SMLoc DirectiveLoc,
6283  DirectiveKind DirKind) {
6284  if (TheCondState.TheCond != AsmCond::IfCond &&
6285  TheCondState.TheCond != AsmCond::ElseIfCond)
6286  return Error(DirectiveLoc, "Encountered a .elseif that doesn't follow an"
6287  " .if or an .elseif");
6288  TheCondState.TheCond = AsmCond::ElseIfCond;
6289 
6290  bool LastIgnoreState = false;
6291  if (!TheCondStack.empty())
6292  LastIgnoreState = TheCondStack.back().Ignore;
6293  if (LastIgnoreState || TheCondState.CondMet) {
6294  TheCondState.Ignore = true;
6295  eatToEndOfStatement();
6296  } else {
6297  int64_t ExprValue;
6298  if (parseAbsoluteExpression(ExprValue))
6299  return true;
6300 
6301  if (parseEOL())
6302  return true;
6303 
6304  switch (DirKind) {
6305  default:
6306  llvm_unreachable("unsupported directive");
6307  case DK_ELSEIF:
6308  break;
6309  case DK_ELSEIFE:
6310  ExprValue = ExprValue == 0;
6311  break;
6312  }
6313 
6314  TheCondState.CondMet = ExprValue;
6315  TheCondState.Ignore = !TheCondState.CondMet;
6316  }
6317 
6318  return false;
6319 }

6325  TheCondState.TheCond != AsmCond::ElseIfCond)

6458  return true;

6461  TheCondState.TheCond != AsmCond::ElseIfCond)
6462  return Error(DirectiveLoc, "Encountered an else that doesn't follow an if"

6476 /// parseDirectiveEnd
6477 /// ::= end
6478 bool MasmParser::parseDirectiveEnd(SMLoc DirectiveLoc) {
6479  if (parseEOL())
6480  return true;
6481 
6482  while (Lexer.isNot(AsmToken::Eof))
6483  Lexer.Lex();
6484 
6485  return false;
6486 }

6488 /// parseDirectiveError
6489 /// ::= .err [message]
6490 bool MasmParser::parseDirectiveError(SMLoc DirectiveLoc) {
6491  if (!TheCondStack.empty()) {
6492  if (TheCondStack.back().Ignore) {
6493  eatToEndOfStatement();
6494  return false;
6495  }
6496  }
6497 
6498  std::string Message = ".err directive invoked in source file";
6499  if (Lexer.isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement))
6500  Message = parseStringTo(AsmToken::EndOfStatement);
6501  Lex();
6502 
6503  return Error(DirectiveLoc, Message);
6504 }

6506 /// parseDirectiveErrorIfb
6507 /// ::= .errb textitem[, message]
6508 bool MasmParser::parseDirectiveErrorIfb(SMLoc DirectiveLoc, bool ExpectBlank) {
6509  if (!TheCondStack.empty()) {
6510  if (TheCondStack.back().Ignore) {
6511  eatToEndOfStatement();
6512  return false;
6513  }
6514  }
6515 
6516  std::string Text;
6517  if (parseTextItem(Text))
6518  return Error(getTok().getLoc(), "missing text item in '.errb' directive");
6519 
6520  std::string Message = ".errb directive invoked in source file";
6521  if (Lexer.isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
6522  if (parseToken(AsmToken::Comma))
6523  return addErrorSuffix(" in '.errb' directive");
6524  Message = parseStringTo(AsmToken::EndOfStatement);
6525  }
6526  Lex();
6527 
6528  if (Text.empty() == ExpectBlank)
6529  return Error(DirectiveLoc, Message);
6530  return false;
6531 }

6627  TheCondState.CondMet = ExpectEqual == (String1 == String2);
6628  TheCondState.Ignore = !TheCondState.CondMet;
6629 
6630  if ((CaseInsensitive &&
6631  ExpectEqual == StringRef(String1).equals_insensitive(String2)) ||
6632  (ExpectEqual == (String1 == String2)))

6804 
6805 bool MasmParser::isMacroLikeDirective() {
6806  if (getLexer().is(AsmToken::Identifier)) {
6807  bool IsMacroLike = StringSwitch<bool>(getTok().getIdentifier())
6808  .CasesLower("repeat", "rept", true)
6809  .CaseLower("while", true)
6810  .CasesLower("for", "irp", true)
6811  .CasesLower("forc", "irpc", true)
6812  .Default(false);
6813  if (IsMacroLike)
6814  return true;
6815  }
6816  if (peekTok().is(AsmToken::Identifier) &&
6817  peekTok().getIdentifier().equals_insensitive("macro"))
6818  return true;
6819 
6820  return false;
6821 }
6822 
6823 MCAsmMacro *MasmParser::parseMacroLikeBody(SMLoc DirectiveLoc) {
6824  AsmToken EndToken, StartToken = getTok();
6825 
6826  unsigned NestLevel = 0;
6827  while (true) {
6828  // Check whether we have reached the end of the file.
6829  if (getLexer().is(AsmToken::Eof)) {
6830  printError(DirectiveLoc, "no matching 'endm' in definition");
6831  return nullptr;
6832  }
6833 
6834  if (isMacroLikeDirective())
6835  ++NestLevel;
6836 
6837  // Otherwise, check whether we have reached the endm.
6838  if (Lexer.is(AsmToken::Identifier) &&
6839  getTok().getIdentifier().equals_insensitive("endm")) {
6840  if (NestLevel == 0) {
6841  EndToken = getTok();
6842  Lex();
6843  if (Lexer.isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
6844  printError(getTok().getLoc(), "unexpected token in 'endm' directive");
6845  return nullptr;
6846  }
6847  break;
6848  }
6849  --NestLevel;
6850  }
6851 
6852  // Otherwise, scan till the end of the statement.
6853  eatToEndOfStatement();
6854  }
6855 
6856  const char *BodyStart = StartToken.getLoc().getPointer();
6857  const char *BodyEnd = EndToken.getLoc().getPointer();
6858  StringRef Body = StringRef(BodyStart, BodyEnd - BodyStart);
6859 
6860  // We Are Anonymous.
6861  MacroLikeBodies.emplace_back(StringRef(), Body, MCAsmMacroParameters());
6862  return &MacroLikeBodies.back();
6863 }
6864 
6865 bool MasmParser::expandStatement(SMLoc Loc) {
6866  std::string Body = parseStringTo(AsmToken::EndOfStatement);
6867  SMLoc EndLoc = getTok().getLoc();
6868 
6869  MCAsmMacroParameters Parameters;
6870  MCAsmMacroArguments Arguments;
6871 
6872  StringMap<std::string> BuiltinValues;
6873  for (const auto &S : BuiltinSymbolMap) {
6874  const BuiltinSymbol &Sym = S.getValue();
6875  if (std::optional<std::string> Text = evaluateBuiltinTextMacro(Sym, Loc)) {
6876  BuiltinValues[S.getKey().lower()] = std::move(*Text);
6877  }
6878  }
6879  for (const auto &B : BuiltinValues) {
6880  MCAsmMacroParameter P;
6881  MCAsmMacroArgument A;
6882  P.Name = B.getKey();
6883  P.Required = true;
6884  A.push_back(AsmToken(AsmToken::String, B.getValue()));
6885 
6886  Parameters.push_back(std::move(P));
6887  Arguments.push_back(std::move(A));
6888  }
6889 
6890  for (const auto &V : Variables) {
6891  const Variable &Var = V.getValue();
6892  if (Var.IsText) {
6893  MCAsmMacroParameter P;
6894  MCAsmMacroArgument A;
6895  P.Name = Var.Name;
6896  P.Required = true;
6897  A.push_back(AsmToken(AsmToken::String, Var.TextValue));
6898 
6899  Parameters.push_back(std::move(P));
6900  Arguments.push_back(std::move(A));
6901  }
6902  }
6903  MacroLikeBodies.emplace_back(StringRef(), Body, Parameters);
6904  MCAsmMacro M = MacroLikeBodies.back();
6905 
6906  // Expand the statement in a new buffer.
6907  SmallString<80> Buf;
6908  raw_svector_ostream OS(Buf);
6909  if (expandMacro(OS, M.Body, M.Parameters, Arguments, M.Locals, EndLoc))
6910  return true;
6911  std::unique_ptr<MemoryBuffer> Expansion =
6912  MemoryBuffer::getMemBufferCopy(OS.str(), "<expansion>");
6913 
6914  // Jump to the expanded statement and prime the lexer.
6915  CurBuffer = SrcMgr.AddNewSourceBuffer(std::move(Expansion), EndLoc);
6916  Lexer.setBuffer(SrcMgr.getMemoryBuffer(CurBuffer)->getBuffer());
6917  EndStatementAtEOFStack.push_back(false);
6918  Lex();
6919  return false;
6920 }
6921 
6922 void MasmParser::instantiateMacroLikeBody(MCAsmMacro *M, SMLoc DirectiveLoc,
6923  raw_svector_ostream &OS) {
6924  instantiateMacroLikeBody(M, DirectiveLoc, /*ExitLoc=*/getTok().getLoc(), OS);
6925 }
6926 void MasmParser::instantiateMacroLikeBody(MCAsmMacro *M, SMLoc DirectiveLoc,
6927  SMLoc ExitLoc,
6928  raw_svector_ostream &OS) {
6929  OS << "endm\n";
6930 
6931  std::unique_ptr<MemoryBuffer> Instantiation =
6932  MemoryBuffer::getMemBufferCopy(OS.str(), "<instantiation>");
6933 
6934  // Create the macro instantiation object and add to the current macro
6935  // instantiation stack.
6936  MacroInstantiation *MI = new MacroInstantiation{DirectiveLoc, CurBuffer,
6937  ExitLoc, TheCondStack.size()};
6938  ActiveMacros.push_back(MI);
6939 
6940  // Jump to the macro instantiation and prime the lexer.
6941  CurBuffer = SrcMgr.AddNewSourceBuffer(std::move(Instantiation), SMLoc());
6942  Lexer.setBuffer(SrcMgr.getMemoryBuffer(CurBuffer)->getBuffer());
6943  EndStatementAtEOFStack.push_back(true);
6944  Lex();
6945 }
6946 
6947 /// parseDirectiveRepeat
6948 /// ::= ("repeat" | "rept") count
6949 /// body
6950 /// endm
6951 bool MasmParser::parseDirectiveRepeat(SMLoc DirectiveLoc, StringRef Dir) {
6952  const MCExpr *CountExpr;
6953  SMLoc CountLoc = getTok().getLoc();
6954  if (parseExpression(CountExpr))
6955  return true;
6956 
6957  int64_t Count;
6958  if (!CountExpr->evaluateAsAbsolute(Count, getStreamer().getAssemblerPtr())) {
6959  return Error(CountLoc, "unexpected token in '" + Dir + "' directive");
6960  }
6961 
6962  if (check(Count < 0, CountLoc, "Count is negative") || parseEOL())
6963  return true;
6964 
6965  // Lex the repeat definition.
6966  MCAsmMacro *M = parseMacroLikeBody(DirectiveLoc);
6967  if (!M)
6968  return true;
6969 
6970  // Macro instantiation is lexical, unfortunately. We construct a new buffer
6971  // to hold the macro body with substitutions.
6972  SmallString<256> Buf;
6973  raw_svector_ostream OS(Buf);
6974  while (Count--) {
6975  if (expandMacro(OS, M->Body, std::nullopt, std::nullopt, M->Locals,
6976  getTok().getLoc()))
6977  return true;
6978  }
6979  instantiateMacroLikeBody(M, DirectiveLoc, OS);
6980 
6981  return false;
6982 }
6983 
6984 /// parseDirectiveWhile
6985 /// ::= "while" expression
6986 /// body
6987 /// endm
6988 bool MasmParser::parseDirectiveWhile(SMLoc DirectiveLoc) {
6989  const MCExpr *CondExpr;
6990  SMLoc CondLoc = getTok().getLoc();
6991  if (parseExpression(CondExpr))
6992  return true;
6993 
6994  // Lex the repeat definition.
6995  MCAsmMacro *M = parseMacroLikeBody(DirectiveLoc);
6996  if (!M)
6997  return true;
6998 
6999  // Macro instantiation is lexical, unfortunately. We construct a new buffer
7000  // to hold the macro body with substitutions.
7001  SmallString<256> Buf;
7002  raw_svector_ostream OS(Buf);
7003  int64_t Condition;
7004  if (!CondExpr->evaluateAsAbsolute(Condition, getStreamer().getAssemblerPtr()))
7005  return Error(CondLoc, "expected absolute expression in 'while' directive");
7006  if (Condition) {
7007  // Instantiate the macro, then resume at this directive to recheck the
7008  // condition.
7009  if (expandMacro(OS, M->Body, std::nullopt, std::nullopt, M->Locals,
7010  getTok().getLoc()))
7011  return true;
7012  instantiateMacroLikeBody(M, DirectiveLoc, /*ExitLoc=*/DirectiveLoc, OS);
7013  }
7014 
7015  return false;
7016 }
7017 
7018 /// parseDirectiveFor
7019 /// ::= ("for" | "irp") symbol [":" qualifier], <values>
7020 /// body
7021 /// endm
7022 bool MasmParser::parseDirectiveFor(SMLoc DirectiveLoc, StringRef Dir) {
7023  MCAsmMacroParameter Parameter;
7024  MCAsmMacroArguments A;
7025  if (check(parseIdentifier(Parameter.Name),
7026  "expected identifier in '" + Dir + "' directive"))
7027  return true;
7028 
7029  // Parse optional qualifier (default value, or "req")
7030  if (parseOptionalToken(AsmToken::Colon)) {
7031  if (parseOptionalToken(AsmToken::Equal)) {
7032  // Default value
7033  SMLoc ParamLoc;
7034 
7035  ParamLoc = Lexer.getLoc();
7036  if (parseMacroArgument(nullptr, Parameter.Value))
7037  return true;
7038  } else {
7039  SMLoc QualLoc;
7040  StringRef Qualifier;
7041 
7042  QualLoc = Lexer.getLoc();
7043  if (parseIdentifier(Qualifier))
7044  return Error(QualLoc, "missing parameter qualifier for "
7045  "'" +
7046  Parameter.Name + "' in '" + Dir +
7047  "' directive");
7048 
7049  if (Qualifier.equals_insensitive("req"))
7050  Parameter.Required = true;
7051  else
7052  return Error(QualLoc,
7053  Qualifier + " is not a valid parameter qualifier for '" +
7054  Parameter.Name + "' in '" + Dir + "' directive");
7055  }
7056  }
7057 
7058  if (parseToken(AsmToken::Comma,
7059  "expected comma in '" + Dir + "' directive") ||
7060  parseToken(AsmToken::Less,
7061  "values in '" + Dir +
7062  "' directive must be enclosed in angle brackets"))
7063  return true;
7064 
7065  while (true) {
7066  A.emplace_back();
7067  if (parseMacroArgument(&Parameter, A.back(), /*EndTok=*/AsmToken::Greater))
7068  return addErrorSuffix(" in arguments for '" + Dir + "' directive");
7069 
7070  // If we see a comma, continue, and allow line continuation.
7071  if (!parseOptionalToken(AsmToken::Comma))
7072  break;
7073  parseOptionalToken(AsmToken::EndOfStatement);
7074  }
7075 
7076  if (parseToken(AsmToken::Greater,
7077  "values in '" + Dir +
7078  "' directive must be enclosed in angle brackets") ||
7079  parseEOL())
7080  return true;
7081 
7082  // Lex the for definition.
7083  MCAsmMacro *M = parseMacroLikeBody(DirectiveLoc);
7084  if (!M)
7085  return true;
7086 
7087  // Macro instantiation is lexical, unfortunately. We construct a new buffer
7088  // to hold the macro body with substitutions.
7089  SmallString<256> Buf;
7090  raw_svector_ostream OS(Buf);
7091 
7092  for (const MCAsmMacroArgument &Arg : A) {
7093  if (expandMacro(OS, M->Body, Parameter, Arg, M->Locals, getTok().getLoc()))
7094  return true;
7095  }
7096 
7097  instantiateMacroLikeBody(M, DirectiveLoc, OS);
7098 
7099  return false;
7100 }
7101 
7102 /// parseDirectiveForc
7103 /// ::= ("forc" | "irpc") symbol, <string>
7104 /// body
7105 /// endm
7106 bool MasmParser::parseDirectiveForc(SMLoc DirectiveLoc, StringRef Directive) {
7107  MCAsmMacroParameter Parameter;
7108 
7109  std::string Argument;
7110  if (check(parseIdentifier(Parameter.Name),
7111  "expected identifier in '" + Directive + "' directive") ||
7112  parseToken(AsmToken::Comma,
7113  "expected comma in '" + Directive + "' directive"))
7114  return true;
7115  if (parseAngleBracketString(Argument)) {
7116  // Match ml64.exe; treat all characters to end of statement as a string,
7117  // ignoring comment markers, then discard anything following a space (using
7118  // the C locale).
7119  Argument = parseStringTo(AsmToken::EndOfStatement);
7120  if (getTok().is(AsmToken::EndOfStatement))
7121  Argument += getTok().getString();
7122  size_t End = 0;
7123  for (; End < Argument.size(); ++End) {
7124  if (isSpace(Argument[End]))
7125  break;
7126  }
7127  Argument.resize(End);
7128  }
7129  if (parseEOL())
7130  return true;
7131 
7132  // Lex the irpc definition.
7133  MCAsmMacro *M = parseMacroLikeBody(DirectiveLoc);
7134  if (!M)
7135  return true;
7136 
7137  // Macro instantiation is lexical, unfortunately. We construct a new buffer
7138  // to hold the macro body with substitutions.
7139  SmallString<256> Buf;
7140  raw_svector_ostream OS(Buf);
7141 
7142  StringRef Values(Argument);
7143  for (std::size_t I = 0, End = Values.size(); I != End; ++I) {
7144  MCAsmMacroArgument Arg;
7145  Arg.emplace_back(AsmToken::Identifier, Values.slice(I, I + 1));
7146 
7147  if (expandMacro(OS, M->Body, Parameter, Arg, M->Locals, getTok().getLoc()))
7148  return true;
7149  }
7150 
7151  instantiateMacroLikeBody(M, DirectiveLoc, OS);
7152 
7153  return false;
7154 }
7155 
7156 bool MasmParser::parseDirectiveMSEmit(SMLoc IDLoc, ParseStatementInfo &Info,
7157  size_t Len) {
7158  const MCExpr *Value;
7159  SMLoc ExprLoc = getLexer().getLoc();
7160  if (parseExpression(Value))
7161  return true;
7162  const MCConstantExpr *MCE = dyn_cast<MCConstantExpr>(Value);
7163  if (!MCE)
7164  return Error(ExprLoc, "unexpected expression in _emit");
7165  uint64_t IntValue = MCE->getValue();
7166  if (!isUInt<8>(IntValue) && !isInt<8>(IntValue))
7167  return Error(ExprLoc, "literal value out of range for directive");
7168 
7169  Info.AsmRewrites->emplace_back(AOK_Emit, IDLoc, Len);
7170  return false;
7171 }
7172 
7173 bool MasmParser::parseDirectiveMSAlign(SMLoc IDLoc, ParseStatementInfo &Info) {
7174  const MCExpr *Value;
7175  SMLoc ExprLoc = getLexer().getLoc();
7176  if (parseExpression(Value))
7177  return true;
7178  const MCConstantExpr *MCE = dyn_cast<MCConstantExpr>(Value);
7179  if (!MCE)
7180  return Error(ExprLoc, "unexpected expression in align");
7181  uint64_t IntValue = MCE->getValue();
7182  if (!isPowerOf2_64(IntValue))
7183  return Error(ExprLoc, "literal value not a power of two greater then zero");
7184 
7185  Info.AsmRewrites->emplace_back(AOK_Align, IDLoc, 5, Log2_64(IntValue));
7186  return false;
7187 }
7188 
7189 bool MasmParser::parseDirectiveRadix(SMLoc DirectiveLoc) {
7190  const SMLoc Loc = getLexer().getLoc();
7191  std::string RadixStringRaw = parseStringTo(AsmToken::EndOfStatement);
7192  StringRef RadixString = StringRef(RadixStringRaw).trim();
7193  unsigned Radix;
7194  if (RadixString.getAsInteger(10, Radix)) {
7195  return Error(Loc,
7196  "radix must be a decimal number in the range 2 to 16; was " +
7197  RadixString);
7198  }
7199  if (Radix < 2 || Radix > 16)
7200  return Error(Loc, "radix must be in the range 2 to 16; was " +
7201  std::to_string(Radix));
7202  getLexer().setMasmDefaultRadix(Radix);
7203  return false;
7204 }

7206 /// parseDirectiveEcho
7207 /// ::= "echo" message
7208 bool MasmParser::parseDirectiveEcho(SMLoc DirectiveLoc) {
7209  std::string Message = parseStringTo(AsmToken::EndOfStatement);
7210  llvm::outs() << Message;
7211  if (!StringRef(Message).endswith("\n"))
7212  llvm::outs() << '\n';
7213  return false;
7214 }
7215 
7216 // We are comparing pointers, but the pointers are relative to a single string.
7217 // Thus, this should always be deterministic.
7218 static int rewritesSort(const AsmRewrite *AsmRewriteA,
7219  const AsmRewrite *AsmRewriteB) {
7220  if (AsmRewriteA->Loc.getPointer() < AsmRewriteB->Loc.getPointer())
7221  return -1;
7222  if (AsmRewriteB->Loc.getPointer() < AsmRewriteA->Loc.getPointer())
7223  return 1;
7224 
7225  // It's possible to have a SizeDirective, Imm/ImmPrefix and an Input/Output
7226  // rewrite to the same location. Make sure the SizeDirective rewrite is
7227  // performed first, then the Imm/ImmPrefix and finally the Input/Output. This
7228  // ensures the sort algorithm is stable.
7229  if (AsmRewritePrecedence[AsmRewriteA->Kind] >
7230  AsmRewritePrecedence[AsmRewriteB->Kind])
7231  return -1;
7232 
7233  if (AsmRewritePrecedence[AsmRewriteA->Kind] <
7234  AsmRewritePrecedence[AsmRewriteB->Kind])
7235  return 1;
7236  llvm_unreachable("Unstable rewrite sort.");
7237 }
7238 
7239 bool MasmParser::defineMacro(StringRef Name, StringRef Value) {
7240  Variable &Var = Variables[Name.lower()];
7241  if (Var.Name.empty()) {
7242  Var.Name = Name;
7243  } else if (Var.Redefinable == Variable::NOT_REDEFINABLE) {
7244  return Error(SMLoc(), "invalid variable redefinition");
7245  } else if (Var.Redefinable == Variable::WARN_ON_REDEFINITION &&
7246  Warning(SMLoc(), "redefining '" + Name +
7247  "', already defined on the command line")) {
7248  return true;
7249  }
7250  Var.Redefinable = Variable::WARN_ON_REDEFINITION;
7251  Var.IsText = true;
7252  Var.TextValue = Value.str();
7253  return false;
7254 }
7255 
7256 bool MasmParser::lookUpField(StringRef Name, AsmFieldInfo &Info) const {
7257  const std::pair<StringRef, StringRef> BaseMember = Name.split('.');
7258  const StringRef Base = BaseMember.first, Member = BaseMember.second;
7259  return lookUpField(Base, Member, Info);
7260 }
7261 
7262 bool MasmParser::lookUpField(StringRef Base, StringRef Member,
7263  AsmFieldInfo &Info) const {
7264  if (Base.empty())
7265  return true;
7266 
7267  AsmFieldInfo BaseInfo;
7268  if (Base.contains('.') && !lookUpField(Base, BaseInfo))
7269  Base = BaseInfo.Type.Name;
7270 
7271  auto StructIt = Structs.find(Base.lower());
7272  auto TypeIt = KnownType.find(Base.lower());
7273  if (TypeIt != KnownType.end()) {
7274  StructIt = Structs.find(TypeIt->second.Name.lower());
7275  }
7276  if (StructIt != Structs.end())
7277  return lookUpField(StructIt->second, Member, Info);
7278 
7279  return true;
7280 }
7281 
7282 bool MasmParser::lookUpField(const StructInfo &Structure, StringRef Member,
7283  AsmFieldInfo &Info) const {
7284  if (Member.empty()) {
7285  Info.Type.Name = Structure.Name;
7286  Info.Type.Size = Structure.Size;
7287  Info.Type.ElementSize = Structure.Size;
7288  Info.Type.Length = 1;
7289  return false;
7290  }
7291 
7292  std::pair<StringRef, StringRef> Split = Member.split('.');
7293  const StringRef FieldName = Split.first, FieldMember = Split.second;
7294 
7295  auto StructIt = Structs.find(FieldName.lower());
7296  if (StructIt != Structs.end())
7297  return lookUpField(StructIt->second, FieldMember, Info);
7298 
7299  auto FieldIt = Structure.FieldsByName.find(FieldName.lower());
7300  if (FieldIt == Structure.FieldsByName.end())
7301  return true;
7302 
7303  const FieldInfo &Field = Structure.Fields[FieldIt->second];
7304  if (FieldMember.empty()) {
7305  Info.Offset += Field.Offset;
7306  Info.Type.Size = Field.SizeOf;
7307  Info.Type.ElementSize = Field.Type;
7308  Info.Type.Length = Field.LengthOf;
7309  if (Field.Contents.FT == FT_STRUCT)
7310  Info.Type.Name = Field.Contents.StructInfo.Structure.Name;
7311  else
7312  Info.Type.Name = "";
7313  return false;
7314  }
7315 
7316  if (Field.Contents.FT != FT_STRUCT)
7317  return true;
7318  const StructFieldInfo &StructInfo = Field.Contents.StructInfo;
7319 
7320  if (lookUpField(StructInfo.Structure, FieldMember, Info))
7321  return true;
7322 
7323  Info.Offset += Field.Offset;
7324  return false;
7325 }
7326 
7327 bool MasmParser::lookUpType(StringRef Name, AsmTypeInfo &Info) const {
7328  unsigned Size = StringSwitch<unsigned>(Name)
7329  .CasesLower("byte", "db", "sbyte", 1)
7330  .CasesLower("word", "dw", "sword", 2)
7331  .CasesLower("dword", "dd", "sdword", 4)
7332  .CasesLower("fword", "df", 6)
7333  .CasesLower("qword", "dq", "sqword", 8)
7334  .CaseLower("real4", 4)
7335  .CaseLower("real8", 8)
7336  .CaseLower("real10", 10)
7337  .Default(0);
7338  if (Size) {
7339  Info.Name = Name;
7340  Info.ElementSize = Size;
7341  Info.Length = 1;
7342  Info.Size = Size;
7343  return false;
7344  }
7345 
7346  auto StructIt = Structs.find(Name.lower());
7347  if (StructIt != Structs.end()) {
7348  const StructInfo &Structure = StructIt->second;
7349  Info.Name = Name;
7350  Info.ElementSize = Structure.Size;
7351  Info.Length = 1;
7352  Info.Size = Structure.Size;
7353  return false;
7354  }
7355 
7356  return true;
7357 }
7358 
7359 bool MasmParser::parseMSInlineAsm(
7360  std::string &AsmString, unsigned &NumOutputs, unsigned &NumInputs,
7361  SmallVectorImpl<std::pair<void *, bool>> &OpDecls,
7362  SmallVectorImpl<std::string> &Constraints,
7363  SmallVectorImpl<std::string> &Clobbers, const MCInstrInfo *MII,
7364  const MCInstPrinter *IP, MCAsmParserSemaCallback &SI) {
7365  SmallVector<void *, 4> InputDecls;
7366  SmallVector<void *, 4> OutputDecls;
7367  SmallVector<bool, 4> InputDeclsAddressOf;
7368  SmallVector<bool, 4> OutputDeclsAddressOf;
7369  SmallVector<std::string, 4> InputConstraints;
7370  SmallVector<std::string, 4> OutputConstraints;
7371  SmallVector<unsigned, 4> ClobberRegs;
7372 
7373  SmallVector<AsmRewrite, 4> AsmStrRewrites;
7374 
7375  // Prime the lexer.
7376  Lex();
7377 
7378  // While we have input, parse each statement.
7379  unsigned InputIdx = 0;
7380  unsigned OutputIdx = 0;
7381  while (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::Eof)) {
7382  // Parse curly braces marking block start/end.
7383  if (parseCurlyBlockScope(AsmStrRewrites))
7384  continue;
7385 
7386  ParseStatementInfo Info(&AsmStrRewrites);
7387  bool StatementErr = parseStatement(Info, &SI);
7388 
7389  if (StatementErr || Info.ParseError) {
7390  // Emit pending errors if any exist.
7391  printPendingErrors();
7392  return true;
7393  }
7394 
7395  // No pending error should exist here.
7396  assert(!hasPendingError() && "unexpected error from parseStatement");
7397 
7398  if (Info.Opcode == ~0U)
7399  continue;
7400 
7401  const MCInstrDesc &Desc = MII->get(Info.Opcode);
7402 
7403  // Build the list of clobbers, outputs and inputs.
7404  for (unsigned i = 1, e = Info.ParsedOperands.size(); i != e; ++i) {
7405  MCParsedAsmOperand &Operand = *Info.ParsedOperands[i];
7406 
7407  // Register operand.
7408  if (Operand.isReg() && !Operand.needAddressOf() &&
7409  !getTargetParser().OmitRegisterFromClobberLists(Operand.getReg())) {
7410  unsigned NumDefs = Desc.getNumDefs();
7411  // Clobber.
7412  if (NumDefs && Operand.getMCOperandNum() < NumDefs)
7413  ClobberRegs.push_back(Operand.getReg());
7414  continue;
7415  }
7416 
7417  // Expr/Input or Output.
7418  StringRef SymName = Operand.getSymName();
7419  if (SymName.empty())
7420  continue;
7421 
7422  void *OpDecl = Operand.getOpDecl();
7423  if (!OpDecl)
7424  continue;
7425 
7426  StringRef Constraint = Operand.getConstraint();
7427  if (Operand.isImm()) {
7428  // Offset as immediate.
7429  if (Operand.isOffsetOfLocal())
7430  Constraint = "r";
7431  else
7432  Constraint = "i";
7433  }
7434 
7435  bool isOutput = (i == 1) && Desc.mayStore();
7436  SMLoc Start = SMLoc::getFromPointer(SymName.data());
7437  if (isOutput) {
7438  ++InputIdx;
7439  OutputDecls.push_back(OpDecl);
7440  OutputDeclsAddressOf.push_back(Operand.needAddressOf());
7441  OutputConstraints.push_back(("=" + Constraint).str());
7442  AsmStrRewrites.emplace_back(AOK_Output, Start, SymName.size());
7443  } else {
7444  InputDecls.push_back(OpDecl);
7445  InputDeclsAddressOf.push_back(Operand.needAddressOf());
7446  InputConstraints.push_back(Constraint.str());
7447  if (Desc.operands()[i - 1].isBranchTarget())
7448  AsmStrRewrites.emplace_back(AOK_CallInput, Start, SymName.size());
7449  else
7450  AsmStrRewrites.emplace_back(AOK_Input, Start, SymName.size());
7451  }
7452  }
7453 
7454  // Consider implicit defs to be clobbers. Think of cpuid and push.
7455  llvm::append_range(ClobberRegs, Desc.implicit_defs());
7456  }
7457 
7458  // Set the number of Outputs and Inputs.
7459  NumOutputs = OutputDecls.size();
7460  NumInputs = InputDecls.size();
7461 
7462  // Set the unique clobbers.
7463  array_pod_sort(ClobberRegs.begin(), ClobberRegs.end());
7464  ClobberRegs.erase(std::unique(ClobberRegs.begin(), ClobberRegs.end()),
7465  ClobberRegs.end());
7466  Clobbers.assign(ClobberRegs.size(), std::string());
7467  for (unsigned I = 0, E = ClobberRegs.size(); I != E; ++I) {
7468  raw_string_ostream OS(Clobbers[I]);
7469  IP->printRegName(OS, ClobberRegs[I]);
7470  }
7471 
7472  // Merge the various outputs and inputs. Output are expected first.
7473  if (NumOutputs || NumInputs) {
7474  unsigned NumExprs = NumOutputs + NumInputs;
7475  OpDecls.resize(NumExprs);
7476  Constraints.resize(NumExprs);
7477  for (unsigned i = 0; i < NumOutputs; ++i) {
7478  OpDecls[i] = std::make_pair(OutputDecls[i], OutputDeclsAddressOf[i]);
7479  Constraints[i] = OutputConstraints[i];
7480  }
7481  for (unsigned i = 0, j = NumOutputs; i < NumInputs; ++i, ++j) {
7482  OpDecls[j] = std::make_pair(InputDecls[i], InputDeclsAddressOf[i]);
7483  Constraints[j] = InputConstraints[i];
7484  }
7485  }
7486 
7487  // Build the IR assembly string.
7488  std::string AsmStringIR;
7489  raw_string_ostream OS(AsmStringIR);
7490  StringRef ASMString =
7491  SrcMgr.getMemoryBuffer(SrcMgr.getMainFileID())->getBuffer();
7492  const char *AsmStart = ASMString.begin();
7493  const char *AsmEnd = ASMString.end();
7494  array_pod_sort(AsmStrRewrites.begin(), AsmStrRewrites.end(), rewritesSort);
7495  for (auto it = AsmStrRewrites.begin(); it != AsmStrRewrites.end(); ++it) {
7496  const AsmRewrite &AR = *it;
7497  // Check if this has already been covered by another rewrite...
7498  if (AR.Done)
7499  continue;
7500  AsmRewriteKind Kind = AR.Kind;
7501 
7502  const char *Loc = AR.Loc.getPointer();
7503  assert(Loc >= AsmStart && "Expected Loc to be at or after Start!");
7504 
7505  // Emit everything up to the immediate/expression.
7506  if (unsigned Len = Loc - AsmStart)
7507  OS << StringRef(AsmStart, Len);
7508 
7509  // Skip the original expression.
7510  if (Kind == AOK_Skip) {
7511  AsmStart = Loc + AR.Len;
7512  continue;
7513  }
7514 
7515  unsigned AdditionalSkip = 0;
7516  // Rewrite expressions in $N notation.
7517  switch (Kind) {
7518  default:
7519  break;
7520  case AOK_IntelExpr:
7521  assert(AR.IntelExp.isValid() && "cannot write invalid intel expression");
7522  if (AR.IntelExp.NeedBracs)
7523  OS << "[";
7524  if (AR.IntelExp.hasBaseReg())
7525  OS << AR.IntelExp.BaseReg;
7526  if (AR.IntelExp.hasIndexReg())
7527  OS << (AR.IntelExp.hasBaseReg() ? " + " : "")
7528  << AR.IntelExp.IndexReg;
7529  if (AR.IntelExp.Scale > 1)
7530  OS << " * $$" << AR.IntelExp.Scale;
7531  if (AR.IntelExp.hasOffset()) {
7532  if (AR.IntelExp.hasRegs())
7533  OS << " + ";
7534  // Fuse this rewrite with a rewrite of the offset name, if present.
7535  StringRef OffsetName = AR.IntelExp.OffsetName;
7536  SMLoc OffsetLoc = SMLoc::getFromPointer(AR.IntelExp.OffsetName.data());
7537  size_t OffsetLen = OffsetName.size();
7538  auto rewrite_it = std::find_if(
7539  it, AsmStrRewrites.end(), [&](const AsmRewrite &FusingAR) {
7540  return FusingAR.Loc == OffsetLoc && FusingAR.Len == OffsetLen &&
7541  (FusingAR.Kind == AOK_Input ||
7542  FusingAR.Kind == AOK_CallInput);
7543  });
7544  if (rewrite_it == AsmStrRewrites.end()) {
7545  OS << "offset " << OffsetName;
7546  } else if (rewrite_it->Kind == AOK_CallInput) {
7547  OS << "${" << InputIdx++ << ":P}";
7548  rewrite_it->Done = true;
7549  } else {
7550  OS << '$' << InputIdx++;
7551  rewrite_it->Done = true;
7552  }
7553  }
7554  if (AR.IntelExp.Imm || AR.IntelExp.emitImm())
7555  OS << (AR.IntelExp.emitImm() ? "$$" : " + $$") << AR.IntelExp.Imm;
7556  if (AR.IntelExp.NeedBracs)
7557  OS << "]";
7558  break;
7559  case AOK_Label:
7560  OS << Ctx.getAsmInfo()->getPrivateLabelPrefix() << AR.Label;
7561  break;
7562  case AOK_Input:
7563  OS << '$' << InputIdx++;
7564  break;
7565  case AOK_CallInput:
7566  OS << "${" << InputIdx++ << ":P}";
7567  break;
7568  case AOK_Output:
7569  OS << '$' << OutputIdx++;
7570  break;
7571  case AOK_SizeDirective:
7572  switch (AR.Val) {
7573  default: break;
7574  case 8: OS << "byte ptr "; break;
7575  case 16: OS << "word ptr "; break;
7576  case 32: OS << "dword ptr "; break;
7577  case 64: OS << "qword ptr "; break;
7578  case 80: OS << "xword ptr "; break;
7579  case 128: OS << "xmmword ptr "; break;
7580  case 256: OS << "ymmword ptr "; break;
7581  }
7582  break;
7583  case AOK_Emit:
7584  OS << ".byte";
7585  break;
7586  case AOK_Align: {
7587  // MS alignment directives are measured in bytes. If the native assembler
7588  // measures alignment in bytes, we can pass it straight through.
7589  OS << ".align";
7590  if (getContext().getAsmInfo()->getAlignmentIsInBytes())
7591  break;
7592 
7593  // Alignment is in log2 form, so print that instead and skip the original
7594  // immediate.
7595  unsigned Val = AR.Val;
7596  OS << ' ' << Val;
7597  assert(Val < 10 && "Expected alignment less then 2^10.");
7598  AdditionalSkip = (Val < 4) ? 2 : Val < 7 ? 3 : 4;
7599  break;
7600  }
7601  case AOK_EVEN:
7602  OS << ".even";
7603  break;
7604  case AOK_EndOfStatement:
7605  OS << "\n\t";
7606  break;
7607  }
7608 
7609  // Skip the original expression.
7610  AsmStart = Loc + AR.Len + AdditionalSkip;
7611  }
7612 
7613  // Emit the remainder of the asm string.
7614  if (AsmStart != AsmEnd)
7615  OS << StringRef(AsmStart, AsmEnd - AsmStart);
7616 
7617  AsmString = OS.str();
7618  return false;
7619 }

7621 void MasmParser::initializeBuiltinSymbolMap() {
7622  // Numeric built-ins (supported in all versions)
7623  BuiltinSymbolMap["@version"] = BI_VERSION;
7624  BuiltinSymbolMap["@line"] = BI_LINE;
7625 
7626  // Text built-ins (supported in all versions)
7627  BuiltinSymbolMap["@date"] = BI_DATE;
7628  BuiltinSymbolMap["@time"] = BI_TIME;
7629  BuiltinSymbolMap["@filecur"] = BI_FILECUR;
7630  BuiltinSymbolMap["@filename"] = BI_FILENAME;
7631  BuiltinSymbolMap["@curseg"] = BI_CURSEG;
7632 
7633  // Some built-ins exist only for MASM32 (32-bit x86)
7634  if (getContext().getSubtargetInfo()->getTargetTriple().getArch() ==
7635  Triple::x86) {
7636  // Numeric built-ins
7637  // BuiltinSymbolMap["@cpu"] = BI_CPU;
7638  // BuiltinSymbolMap["@interface"] = BI_INTERFACE;
7639  // BuiltinSymbolMap["@wordsize"] = BI_WORDSIZE;
7640  // BuiltinSymbolMap["@codesize"] = BI_CODESIZE;
7641  // BuiltinSymbolMap["@datasize"] = BI_DATASIZE;
7642  // BuiltinSymbolMap["@model"] = BI_MODEL;
7643 
7644  // Text built-ins
7645  // BuiltinSymbolMap["@code"] = BI_CODE;
7646  // BuiltinSymbolMap["@data"] = BI_DATA;
7647  // BuiltinSymbolMap["@fardata?"] = BI_FARDATA;
7648  // BuiltinSymbolMap["@stack"] = BI_STACK;
7649  }
7650 }

7652 const MCExpr *MasmParser::evaluateBuiltinValue(BuiltinSymbol Symbol,
7653  SMLoc StartLoc) {
7654  switch (Symbol) {
7655  default:
7656  return nullptr;
7657  case BI_VERSION:
7658  // Match a recent version of ML.EXE.
7659  return MCConstantExpr::create(1427, getContext());
7660  case BI_LINE: {
7661  int64_t Line;
7662  if (ActiveMacros.empty())
7663  Line = SrcMgr.FindLineNumber(StartLoc, CurBuffer);
7664  else
7665  Line = SrcMgr.FindLineNumber(ActiveMacros.front()->InstantiationLoc,
7666  ActiveMacros.front()->ExitBuffer);
7667  return MCConstantExpr::create(Line, getContext());
7668  }
7669  }
7670  llvm_unreachable("unhandled built-in symbol");
7671 }
7672 
7673 std::optional<std::string>
7674 MasmParser::evaluateBuiltinTextMacro(BuiltinSymbol Symbol, SMLoc StartLoc) {
7675  switch (Symbol) {
7676  default:
7677  return {};
7678  case BI_DATE: {
7679  // Current local date, formatted MM/DD/YY
7680  char TmpBuffer[sizeof("mm/dd/yy")];
7681  const size_t Len = strftime(TmpBuffer, sizeof(TmpBuffer), "%D", &TM);
7682  return std::string(TmpBuffer, Len);
7683  }
7684  case BI_TIME: {
7685  // Current local time, formatted HH:MM:SS (24-hour clock)
7686  char TmpBuffer[sizeof("hh:mm:ss")];
7687  const size_t Len = strftime(TmpBuffer, sizeof(TmpBuffer), "%T", &TM);
7688  return std::string(TmpBuffer, Len);
7689  }
7690  case BI_FILECUR:
7691  return SrcMgr
7692  .getMemoryBuffer(
7693  ActiveMacros.empty() ? CurBuffer : ActiveMacros.front()->ExitBuffer)
7694  ->getBufferIdentifier()
7695  .str();
7696  case BI_FILENAME:
7697  return sys::path::stem(SrcMgr.getMemoryBuffer(SrcMgr.getMainFileID())
7698  ->getBufferIdentifier())
7699  .upper();
7700  case BI_CURSEG:
7701  return getStreamer().getCurrentSectionOnly()->getName().str();
7702  }
7703  llvm_unreachable("unhandled built-in symbol");
7704 }
